  render_p(sec, "K-RESONANCE (S1082): K always self-resonates. lambda(K^2=9) = K(K-1) = 6, and K divides 6. This is universal: for any prime p, p divides p(p-1) = lambda(p^2). But D=2 does NOT K-resonate (lambda(8) = 2, K = 3 does not divide 2). In the D^3=8 cube, this makes K = (1,1,1) fully alive while D = (0,0,0) fully dead. The two forbidden cube states (001) and (110) are empty because D and K are the only primes at their respective extremes, and their K-resonance is fixed.");
  render_p(sec, "HAMMING WEIGHT (S1083): K has cube weight 3 -- all three axes positive (alive, survives, K-resonant). D has weight 0. Antipodal weight sum D+K = K. Total weight across all 6 primes = K^2 = 9. Full D^3=8 cube weight = heartbeat (12); forbidden pair removes K; heartbeat - K = K^2. Closure removes itself to create the spider web.");
